The readout of ADC will can be saved into a .csv file
by running the macro: sh save_ADC.sh,
the saving frequence can be changed by changing the number in the .sh file, 
for an example, '/bin/sleep 1' means the saving frequence is 1s for saving one time.

The saving order in .csv file is:
[System time, readout from ADC*[32]]
